#MEM id=vercel-react-best-practices source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/README.md
M|vercel-react-best-practices|A structured repository for creating and maintaining React Best Practices optimized for agents and LLMs.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rules/` - Individual rule files (one per rule)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `_sections.md` - Section metadata (titles, impacts, descriptions)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `_template.md` - Template for creating new rules
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `area-description.md` - Individual rule files
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `src/` - Build scripts and utilities
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `metadata.json` - doc metadata (version, organization, abstract)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- __`AGENTS.md`__ - Compiled output (generated)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- __`test-cases.json`__ - Test cases for LLM evaluation (generated)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|1. Install dependencies:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```bash
M|vercel-react-best-practices|pnpm install
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|2. Build AGENTS.md from rules:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```bash
M|vercel-react-best-practices|pnpm build
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|3. Validate rule files:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```bash
M|vercel-react-best-practices|pnpm validate
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|4. Extract test cases:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```bash
M|vercel-react-best-practices|pnpm extract-tests
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|1. Copy `rules/_template.md` to `rules/area-description.md`
M|vercel-react-best-practices|2. Choose the appropriate area prefix:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `async-` for Eliminating Waterfalls (Section 1)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `bundle-` for Bundle Size Optimization (Section 2)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `server-` for Server-Side Performance (Section 3)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `client-` for Client-Side Data Fetching (Section 4)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rerender-` for Re-render Optimization (Section 5)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `rendering-` for Rendering Performance (Section 6)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `js-` for JavaScript Performance (Section 7)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `advanced-` for Advanced Patterns (Section 8)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|3. Fill in the frontmatter and cnt
M|vercel-react-best-practices|4. Ensure you have clear examples with explanations
M|vercel-react-best-practices|5. Run `pnpm build` to regenerate AGENTS.md and test-cases.json
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Each rule file should follow this structure:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```markdown
M|vercel-react-best-practices|title: Rule Title Here
M|vercel-react-best-practices|impact: MEDIUM
M|vercel-react-best-practices|impactDescription: Optional description
M|vercel-react-best-practices|tags: tag1, tag2, tag3
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Brief explanation of the rule and why it matters.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Incorrect (description of what's wrong):**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Bad code example
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|**Correct (description of what's right):**
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```typescript
M|vercel-react-best-practices|// Good code example
M|vercel-react-best-practices|```
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Optional explanatory text after examples.
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Reference: [Link](https://example.com)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Files starting with `_` are special (excluded from build)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Rule files: `area-description.md` (e.g., `async-parallel.md`)
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Section is automatically inferred from filename prefix
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- Rules are sorted alphabetically by title within each section
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- IDs (e.g., 1.1, 1.2) are auto-generated during build
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `CRITICAL` - Highest priority, major performance gains
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `HIGH` - Significant performance improvements
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `MEDIUM-HIGH` - Moderate-high gains
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `MEDIUM` - Moderate performance improvements
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `LOW-MEDIUM` - Low-medium gains
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `LOW` - Incremental improvements
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `pnpm build` - Compile rules into AGENTS.md
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `pnpm validate` - Validate all rule files
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `pnpm extract-tests` - Extract test cases for LLM evaluation
M|vercel-react-best-practices|- `pnpm dev` - Build and validate
M|vercel-react-best-practices|When adding or modifying rules:
M|vercel-react-best-practices|1. Use the correct filename prefix for your section
M|vercel-react-best-practices|2. Follow the `_template.md` structure
M|vercel-react-best-practices|3. Include clear bad/good examples with explanations
M|vercel-react-best-practices|4. Add appropriate tags
M|vercel-react-best-practices|5. Run `pnpm build` to regenerate AGENTS.md and test-cases.json
M|vercel-react-best-practices|6. Rules are automatically sorted by title - no need to manage numbers!
M|vercel-react-best-practices|Originally created by [@shuding](https://x.com/shuding) at [Vercel](https://vercel.com).